Let's analyze the given data step by step to compute each required financial ratio.

### 1. Free Cash Flow (FCF)
FCF = Operating Cash Flow - Capital Expenditures (CapEx)
- Operating Cash Flow = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 803,237.11
- CapEx = Purchase of Fixed Assets = 437,464.43

FCF = 803,237.11 - 437,464.43 = 365,772.68

### 2. Return on Assets (ROA)
ROA = (Net Income / Total Assets at end) × 100
- Net Income = 1,105,265.77
- Total Assets at end = 15,653,266.97

ROA = (1,105,265.77 / 15,653,266.97) × 100 ≈ 7.06%

### 3. Return on Equity (ROE)
ROE = (Net Income / Total Owner's Equity at end) × 100
- Owner's Equity at end = 14,105,265.77

ROE = (1,105,265.77 / 14,105,265.77) × 100 ≈ 7.84%

### 4. Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio
This ratio indicates how much operating cash flow is generated per unit of net income.
- Operating Cash Flow = 803,237.11
- Net Income = 1,105,265.77

Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Net Income ≈ 803,237.11 / 1,105,265.77 ≈ 0.727 (or 72.7%)

### 5. Net Profit Margin
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
- Net Profit = 1,105,265.77
- Revenue = 5,760,023.09

Margin = (1,105,265.77 / 5,760,023.09) × 100 ≈ 19.20%

### 6. Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
- Gross Profit = 2,620,023.09
- Revenue = 5,760,023.09

Margin = (2,620,023.09 / 5,760,023.09) × 100 ≈ 45.54%

---

}}
